      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Each solver was verified against ASME V&V 10 benchmark problems relevant to structural mechanics. Patch tests and manufactured solution tests confirm correct implementation of linear and nonlinear element formulations used in the pedicle screw model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) on primary QoI (stiffness) must be below 5%.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted on three mesh densities (coarse: 42k elements, medium: 168k elements, fine: 672k elements). GCI on stiffness QoI = 1.8%, on yield force QoI = 2.1%. Richardson extrapolation applied. Observed convergence order p = 1.94, consistent with second-order elements. Discretization error is well controlled."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
