      "rationale": "Iterative solver residuals monitored to 1e-6 for all load steps. Nonlinear Newton-Raphson convergence confirmed with force and displacement norms. No solver divergence events recorded across 33 simulation runs comprising the ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation inputs were reviewed by a second analyst independent of the model builder. Boundary condition application, load magnitudes, and material assignment were verified against the simulation protocol. A formal peer-review checklist (NGA-QA-CHK-007) was completed and archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model adopted for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) screw and UHMWPE block, consistent with the elastic regime of ASTM F1717 testing. Frictional contact (mu = 0.2) applied at screw-block interface. Geometric nonlinearity enabled to capture large-displacement effects at 40 mm endpoint. Model form choices are consistent with published literature and have been peer-reviewed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from manufacturer-supplied certified coupon test data (E = 114 GPa, yield = 880 MPa for Ti-6Al-4V). Geometry digitised from production drawings with dimensional tolerances incorporated via sensitivity analysis. Sensitivity analysis confirmed QoI variation < 1.5% across the tolerance band. Input uncertainty formally quantified and propagated."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 production-representative specimens from the same lot as the device submission. Specimens span two independent laboratories (Lab A: n=6, Lab B: n=5). Dimensional inspection confirmed all specimens within drawing tolerances. Sample size provides 80% power to detect a 10% difference at alpha=0.05."
    },
    {
