      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. Note: this factor is below required level; risk is accepted based on the conservative nature of the single ASTM F1717 load case.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single standardised load condition (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending at 5 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). Only one test condition was evaluated, which limits the achieved level to 2 against a required level of 3. The shortfall is accepted because the ASTM F1717 protocol represents the most demanding standardised condition for this device class, and the clinical loading envelope does not significantly exceed this condition."
    },
