      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to the clinical performance requirements for the pedicle screw construct. These quantities are mechanistically linked to the failure modes of concern (fatigue initiation, permanent deformation)."
