    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level of 3; this shortfall is formally accepted because the ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol is conservative relative to the clinical loading envelope and the remaining factors provide sufficient compensating evidence. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds (relative difference < 10%, E/uval < 1.96). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for the stated COU.",
